<title>JAPAN: Citizen shares rise on news of share buy-backs.</title>
<headline>Citizen shares rise on news of share buy-backs.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Citizen Watch Co Ltd jumped on Friday morning, boosted by the firm's announcement on Thursday that it plans to buy back up to 10 billion yen worth of its own shares.</p>
<p>The share price gained 61 yen to 902 at 0139 GMT. Trading volume was 1.379 million shares.</p>
<p>&quot;Firms which announced share buy-backs have attracted investors recently. Dealers were also joining the buying trend,&quot; said a broker at a second-tier Japanese securities house.</p>
